1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,330
The Universal Declaration of Human Rights is a milestone document in the history of human rights.

2
00:00:05,330 --> 00:00:10,660
Drafted by representatives with different legal and cultural backgrounds from all regions of the world,

3
00:00:10,660 --> 00:00:15,991
the declaration was proclaimed by the United Nations General Assembly in Paris on ten December nineteen forty eight.

4
00:00:15,991 --> 00:00:21,321
It sets out for the first time fundamental human rights to be universally protected.

5
00:00:21,321 --> 00:00:26,652
All human beings are born free and equal in dignity and rights.

6
00:00:26,652 --> 00:00:31,982
They are endowed with reason and conscience and should act towards one another in a spirit of brotherhood.

7
00:00:31,982 --> 00:00:37,312
Everyone has the right to life, liberty and security of person.

8
00:00:37,312 --> 00:00:42,643
No one shall be held in slavery or servitude.

9
00:00:42,643 --> 00:00:47,973
Everyone has the right to freedom of thought, conscience and religion.

10
00:00:47,973 --> 00:00:53,304
Everyone has the right to freedom of opinion and expression.

